    • Enum Constant Detail

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final Notification.Severity UNKNOWN
        Severity is unknown.

      • PANIC

        public static final Notification.Severity PANIC
        A "panic" condition usually affecting multiple apps/servers/sites. At this level it would usually notify all tech staff on call.

      • ALERT

        public static final Notification.Severity ALERT
        Should be corrected immediately, therefore notify staff who can fix the problem. An example would be the loss of a primary ISP connection.

      • CRITICAL

        public static final Notification.Severity CRITICAL
        Should be corrected immediately, but indicates failure in a secondary system, an example is a loss of a backup ISP connection.

      • ERROR

        public static final Notification.Severity ERROR
        Non-urgent failures, these should be relayed to developers or admins; each item must be resolved within a given time.

      • WARNING

        public static final Notification.Severity WARNING
        Warning messages, not an error, but indication that an error will occur if action is not taken, e.g. file system 85% full - each item must be resolved within a given time.

      • NOTICE

        public static final Notification.Severity NOTICE
        Events that are unusual but not error conditions - might be summarized in an email to developers or admins to spot potential problems - no immediate action required.

      • INFO

        public static final Notification.Severity INFO
        Normal operational messages - may be harvested for reporting, measuring throughput, etc. - no action required.

      • DEBUG

        public static final Notification.Severity DEBUG
        Info useful to developers for debugging the application, not useful during operations.
